  * Forrester (required; drop list of Forrester-type Contacts; filters down as you type)
  * Scale (drop-list of International / Doyle; required; default to International; see Other Notes for explanation about International vs. Doyle scales) 
  * Prospectus Comparison (embedded spreadsheet with the following:) 
    * Columns: 
      * Species (auto-filled and read-only; when the Tract record is created, the spreadsheet automatically includes a row for each active Species in the Solution) 
      * # of Trees (optional; number to 0 decimal places
      * Avg DBH (optional; DBH stands for Diameter at Breast Height; number to 1 decimal place; not used for any calculations)
      * Avg BF (auto-calculated and read-only; this = "Total BF" / "# of Trees" for the row)
      * Total BF (required; number to 0 decimal places; user enters "0" if there are no logs for a row)
      * Price/MBF (required; number to 0 decimal places; user enters "0" if there are no logs for a row)
      * Value (auto-calculated and read-only; this = "Total BF" / 1000 x "Price/MBF" for the row)
      * (blank spacer column)
      * Harvested Doyle BF (auto-set and read-only; total board feet for logs of that Species for the Tract)
      * Harvested Avg Price/MBF (auto-set and read-only; average price paid for logs of that Species for the Tract)
      * Harvested Value (auto-set and read-only; actual total value of logs of that Species for the Tract)
      * (blank spacer column)
      * Compare BF (auto-calculated and read-only; this = "Harvested Doyle BF" \- "Total BF")
      * Compare Avg Price (auto-calculated and read-only; this = "Harvested Avg Price/MBF" \- "Price/MBF")
      * Compare Value (auto-calculated and read-only; this = "Harvested Value" \- "Value"
    * Automatically sorted by: Species, with the "Misc." Species at the bottom (sort alphabetically by species, except for "Misc." which is at the bottom)
    * Show 15 rows without scrolling
  * Totals (auto-calculated and read-only; displayed on the screen directly below the corresponding columns):
    * # of Trees (sum)
    * Avg DBH (average; exclude 0s and blanks)
    * Avg BF (average; exclude 0s and blanks)
    * Total BF (sum)
    * Price/MBF (average; exclude 0s and blanks)
    * Value (sum)
